76561198000861562,Recommended,434570,22987317,"Posted: 14 May, 2016",all,Z0mBi3,"This is a simple, silly little game that I picked up late friday night, just to play something while I watched some videos on my other monitor. I picked this game since its fast to download (300mb) , looked like a game that I could easily get into and the price is almost nothing.The graphics are old-looking, but in my opinion kinda charming. The ak-47 looks like something taken out of the counter strike 1.6 era, but the game plays like a fast-paced, crazy FPS, serious sam/shadow warrior sort of game. The graphics was obviously made this was to be more of a humorous type of game.The story doesn't make much sense and the voice-acting is pretty bad, but who cares. This is a game mostly focused on silly gameplay where you murder hordes of monsters and animals for a while. This game actually had more depth then I expected for the price, lots of characters to pick between, some sort of upgrade system, new unlockable levels, cheat mode enabled once you clear 30 waves, and so on.I think the psysics are fun and satisfying in this game. Monster splatter to pieces when you shot them up with a shotgun, and I also tried out a revolver and what looked like a desert eagle pistol. There is some bugs and glitches here and there, but I got some laughs out of this little game anyway. Includes steam trading cards as well, so you can actually make your money back, or close to, by just selling the cards. Also achievements, stats and controller support for those that like that.If you just want a little bit of fun alone or with friends ( yes, it has co-op) then by all means pick this up. Just don't expect to much in terms of graphics or story. Blood and bacon does have 100+ levels though, so gameplay-wise it actually have a lot of content for the asking price.I say like Macklemore, ""but sh*t, it was 99 cents... """
