,Recommended,434570,26183851,"Posted: 23 October, 2016",all,Sweep,"About Blood and BaconBlood and Baconis a simple game that was made for fun, so that friends could get together and just have some fun blowing up giant pigs. There isn't much more than that. But is this game a bloody mess, or does it really bring home the bacon?This Multiplayer (Up To 4P) ""Survival Horror FPS"" has Day and Night levels, players will take on 35 enemy types and numerous bosses, like Gargantuan Monsters and Minibosses every 10 days as you explore, shoot and run for your life against the onslaught of porcine monstrosities.The StoryYou and/or a couple of your friends are trapped at a farm in a barn along with The Farmer, who is nailed to the wall with a pitchfork. He's actually pretty funny, and his monotone voice works with that really well. He has a ton of guns and ammo in the barn for you to go out each day and destroy the demon pigs that have taken over his farm. That's really it. This game doesn't have or need much story. You go outside and blow up pigs. It's goofy and it works really well.GameplayThe game itself is very fun to put it short. Expecially with friends, which is what the game was made for. Each day there is a number of pigs outside on the farm, and your goal is to destroy them all. It's super bloody and bits of pig go everywhere. On the farm there are water pumps that heal you, and electric fence you can activate to fry pigs, and a huge meat grinder, that you can push pigs into to get grenades, ammo, etc. There are a few secrets to find as well. Like I said earlier, the game is very L4D, so you have a primary and secondary you can grab from the barn each day, unlocking more every so often for more pure carnitage (I had to). If you run out of health, you fall down into last stand mode where a friend must pick you up. It's silly, bloody, and really fun to play with a friend or three.All in All Blood and Bacon is a really nice Action Game!9/10 From MeSweep"
