76561198271005884,Recommended,434570,33511052,Posted: 13 July,all,Catnip,"I've been playing Blood and Bacon for a while now and have completed the game twice in hard mode. I guess it's safe to say I have experience with this game.The MechanicsThe mechanics in Blood and Bacon are simple. W A S D to move. Aim with the mouse. Left click to shoot. Q to switch between Primary and Secondary. And, space to jump. Fairly easy to get used to.The StoryI can't really type much here because of how little the story is imprinted into the actual game. All I know is that you're a police officer (Or daughter, Scarecrow, Robot or Skeleton.) Who is trying to save a farmer who has a pitchfork through him. You have to kill savage pigs outside of a barn. That's it. It's kinda like Left 4 Dead in a way.The GraphicsIf anyone has watched the trailers and/or gameplays. You would know.Final ThoughtsIn conclusion Blood and Bacon is a good game and a brilliant way to kill time. The story might not be too in depth but everything else is made up for that.RatingI would rate this a 9/10."
