,Recommended,434570,23041401,"Posted: 17 May, 2016",all,Frank and Sinatra,"Firstly getting into start screen. The start screen is very basic, but it's very well done. It's easy to find the graphic settings, the controls, the co-op, and single player buttons, not to mention the audio itself.Getting into the actual gameplay, It's amazing. Although the farmer is very annoying, but for what you pay for the game it is really good. The guns are really good, and powerful at low rounds, and as you progress it gets harder to kill the boars. Getting into the days, I think 101 days is a little bit long to play, but if you have the time it's fun, and the characters themselves are great to play as.The bosses get harder every 10 days which is really challenging and fun. I love the aspect that they can heal so that they don't die so easily, and you have to actually do a lot of hard work to kill them, but the best part of the bosses is the names for the fat pig that's in the middle.Getting on to the grinder. The grinder is amazing, but it is used for powerups which is also a great addition to the game, and make sit much better to play for something else other than just killing boars that are on steroids, but apart from that stuff that's all there is to the grinder.Getting on the farmer himself. He is funny, but also annoying. His jokes aren't that great, and could be worked on a little bit, but apart from that the farmer is a great guy. Especially when you shoot him, and he starts getting mad, and eventually throws stuff at you.Getting on the boars. There is a mix of boar's from small to large, and from skeletons, to bosses, and from boar's to pigs. The game on a whole is amazing, and I love it.Getting on to the price. The price of the game should be more, because of how fun the game is especially when you play with friends, and have a laugh with them. So I recommend the price should be set atleast at £2.50, and not 0.75. I'm not complaining about it being so cheap, but I think it should be more.On a whole I would recommend anyone to get this game that enjoys shooter genres, and loves to play co-op with friends.I would rate this game a 10/10, and that you should buy it if you have a spare £0.79P.S. Sorry for this long review. :)"
