,Recommended,434570,24404454,"Posted: 19 July, 2016",all,Spectre,"Blood and Bacon is a Nex-Generation survival/shooter game that pits you against swarms of undead boars which have seemingly overrun a strange and remote farm. You, a mysterious stranger must assist a Farmer... tormented by the evil he has unwittingly unleashed upon this land, surviving round after round hordes of blood thirsty swine. You can feel the pain and anguish the Farmer feels as he pleads with you to help cleanse his farm from the armies of boars that gather upon his barns doorsteps daily... as they grow ever so stronger each day. You will be moved to tears as hear him pitifully try to be optimistic in this hell... cracking jokes to keep your spirits going as he hangs there, slowly bleeding to death in agonizing pain from a pitchfork pierced deep within his gut.The stunning graphics make it all look almost real as I've never seen a game looked quite this gorgeous, the attention to detail the developers gave is incredible to say the least. The voice acting is phenominal and is deserving of an Oscar as I felt a connection with the farmer... I empathized his struggle and knew exaclty what he was feeling... regret for his sins... the feeling of hanging onto whatever sliver of optimism you can in a dark and seemingly hopeless hell in which he is living in. The futility of struggle as every time you conquer an army of hell spawn, the next day brings upon an even greater obstacle than the last, but you must tread on... for the Farmer...The story is filled with action, drama, and mystery as you must battle your way forward... day and night to uncover the truth of what happened here... slaughtering tens of thousands of swine by your hand, for you shall become death incarnate...Mortem Incarnatum..."
