76561198048974498,Recommended,434570,20900988,"Posted: 1 February, 2016",all,rjmacready,"Isn't it funny how these things seem to roam in packs?  It's been less than a week since the pig-tastic Iron Snout found its way onto Steam, and now we have more bloodthirsty porcine madness in the form of Blood and Bacon.  My opinion of this game?  It's quite simply one of the dumbest, yet funnest, games you're ever liable to play.  Yeah, it's stoopid.  Stoopid and bloody and gross.  And sure the graphics aren't exactly ""next-gen"".  But if you're looking for something silly to satisfy the Serious Sam in you, this game will do just the trick.  All this, and it's only a ♥♥♥♥ING DOLLAR!Let me put it some other ways.  Have you ever felt like being vomited and projectile♥♥♥♥♥♥upon by a gigantic pig called Princess Blubbergut?  Yeah, me neither, but turns out it's actually pretty fun.  Ever wanted a game where shooting enemies not only in the face but in the♥♥♥♥♥does more damage than standard shots?  Yup, you get the idea.  All this, and missions handed out by a farmer pinned to a barn wall by a pitchfork, who somehow never seems to die for weeks on end.  You can even shoot him repeatedly in the face for an achievement!In short, almost everything about this game is pretty hilarious:  The gore, the achievements, the farmer's dialogue, the voice acting.  This game basically achieves everything it sets out to achieve, and that's a rare thing these days, even when a game's ambitions aren't incredibly high.  My only complaint is that it was initially a bit of a trick to get the thing to go full-screen and to work out some of the keys - it was designed more for X-Box and a controller - but hopefully the dev will sort that stuff out soon.  Entertaining, unpretentious, and dirt-cheap.  If only more ""Big Corporation""s behaved this way!Verdict: 8/10."
