76561198006541362,Recommended,434570,22119516,"Posted: 29 March, 2016",all,stranger1982,"You're tasked with clearing a farm where boars and other livestock have gone crazy and grown quite resilient (possibly undead): your only company in all this is the farm owner who seems to be quite happy with being stuck on a wall with a pitchfork in its chest.What follows is a basic but enjoyable wave shooter where you must survive for 101 days against porcine foes and bosses, either alone or in co-op: the actual gameplay is quite barebones but fun enough especially in short bursts.PROS:-the silly premise works well and is quite funny-the over the top gore and amount of gibs can get quite hilarious, same goes for the game's brand of humour (which goes from childish to toilet)-there's at least some attempts at providing variety thanks to a few different enemy models/ types-provides a fair to intense challenge depending on difficulty level and/ or whether you're alone or in co-op-the short day duration, with most being complete in a couple minutes, makes it perfect for a quick play-if you can stomach the basic, unvaried gameplay there's quite alot to play through as the 101 days'll take at least 5 hours to completeCONS:-the low production values are evident in the simple graphics and sounds-gets repetitive pretty fast due to the lack of variety and single game area-a few difficulty spikeshttp://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=652505338Blood and Bacon is pretty polarizing when it comes to enjoying it as you'll either appreciate its simple, gory, shoot-a-ton-o-stuff mindset or dislike it for its basicness, repetitiveness and toiler humor. There's really no way around it as you'll be doing mostly the same thing for most waves (that is, shooting purcines until they die/ gib/ explode while trying not to be gored to death): some variety can come from armored enemies that you must shoot in the back or bosses that require a bit of strategy but that's all.Said repetitiveness is also made stronger by the overall lack of different enemy models and the fact you'll be seeing the same two bosses types over and over every ten days with- at most- only slight changes in how they work.As for what it does right well, the game is extremely easy to pick up and play and the fact each day is so short means you can give it a quick go even if you have little time. The toilet humor can be funny at times- if you're ok with that brand of humor ofc- and the huge amount of gibs/ blood on screen is as amusing as it is satisfying to see after you've managed to clear a particularly hard day. While basic the gameplay can also be quite challenging especially when playing solo as certain enemies can kill you in a few hits if you let them get too close: same goes for bosses as they'll require a good amount of concentration to succeed.For me Blood and Bacon was a fun yet slightly dull and somewhat forgettable experience, an one trick pony if you wish: but for a dollar I feel I got enough enjoyment from it to justify its purchase hence my thumbs up. As for you well, it's quite decent if you're looking for something silly to play in short bursts, even more so with a friend."
