76561198103073855,Recommended,434570,24215680,"Posted: 9 July, 2016",all,AnionShade,"Blood and Bacon is a indie game that is unique to say the least. It may not be the most AAA title from popular developers, but that does not make this game just as good. Not only did this game meet my standards but also exceeded. This game when above and beyond the Call of Duty (which this game is nothing like).Story- well to say the least of the story, there is one that i haven't exactly found out. This games story makes you really dig deep into the game, as they did not just do cut scenes and put the story out in the open. I personally like this approach to the game, as this makes the game more deep then you would think on first hand when playing the game.Game play-The single player was fun to play through without cheats, although cheats are a totally viable option (if you want every day to be revenge day). I couldn't test the multi player as i didn't have any friends who play this game. However- they put in a whole alpha phase to the multi player (meaning it is currently being tested) and they put in a harder game mode for the multi player if you want to, along with server commands. If you have friends, play it with them, it will only make the game more enjoyable. Single player is just as fun however, so either way you can not go wrong. The weapons in the game are just as good as you would expect them to be in other shooters. They are balanced, fun and easy to use, and not one gun is better then the other, so its all based on how you want to play. Although the number of guns you get are small, this is a good thing, so you are not over whelmed with what to pick and choose. Hit boxes are up to standards with other games.  This game also has gore to it, as the title suggests, meaning body parts go flying if the enemy is shot the right way. You can also kick them and complete an achievement with them.Sound-The sound in this game is very well made. This isn't a shooter that is supposed to be realistic, so don't go judging the game on that end. Instead, judge it on how clear the sound is. The sound is very clear  to say the least. There is also no sound delay, so you wont feel like the sound is lagging (this can be very frustrating)Graphics-Although the graphics are not like Destiny or Fall Out 4 on the PC, this game is not supposed to be like that. The graphics were made to please the eye, while also being not so strong that you cant play it on non gaming or old PCs, or even a laptop. I got 60 Frames Per Second (FPS) while played this game every time I did. I never Experienced any lag except if I had a browser open while playing, but this is because my laptop is not the most graphically enhanced. This game is about the experience, and not the power about it (even an achievement for turning up the ""graphics"" lol).Over all rating-If you like shooter games, this does not fall below even the most modern shooters. This game visually gives me a vibe of Retro games like Left 4 Dead, while still giving me a sensation that describes the most modern games.This game could have easily been priced up to 30 dollars for how good it is, but the developers decided to put the game to just a dollar, to make a profit off of the game but still be affordable so everyone could play the game.Rating 10/10. Recommended for people who like: Shooters, arcade games, multi player games, and value games."
