,Recommended,434570,21093761,"Posted: 9 February, 2016",all,Exxor: Killer Drake,"I picked it up for 99 cents before the deal started; I have to say I still feel I got my money's worth, and more! I thought that was good,  so 74 cents is a real steal. GET IT NOW!  :) The devs are adding new content every week, and they listen to the players; which is too often a rarity nowadays.If you're a fan of Jim Sterling, you'll love this game since he voices the farmer stuck to the wall by a pitchfork. There's a variety of crazy characters to choose from; the roster is going up with them, as well as weapons, and craftable powerups. Power ups can be made by using A Machine For Pigs (meat grinder) if you'll pardon the bad pun; you make stuff by kicking pig parts into it.This is also a survival game if you haven't guessed; it is a welcome twist on the genre to add humor. The most you could be terrified is when facing either the hordes of undead pigs, or bosses in the dark, with a flashlight. It's all good fun, but messy. :)Plus, it's possible to reload while running, and they just recently added fov settings among other things.Overall, I greatly enjoyed it, but if you have a problem with the porcine slaughter of thousands of not so innocent pigs then this is not the game for you."
