76561198070396133,Recommended,434570,22051658,"Posted: 25 March, 2016",all,ｓａｄｂｏｉ,"If Postal 2 and L4D2 had a baby that had pigsBlood and Bacon was one of those games that I did look down upon at first until I had actually played it and I really enjoyed it, so apologies to the developers. This game offers a great amount of gameplay and quirky comedy that will leave you playing for hours.GameplayThe gameplay is surprisingly fun. You're given a (somewhat) wide selection of weapons to choose from and each day you're given a certain amount of enemies to kill and the rest of what you can do is up to you. It's amazing each day, you can experiment different ways to kill the pigs (deadly pigs). With pig parts flying all over you can move them to the grinder where you can pick up things such as ammo, boar milk, and so much more. The game also has certain challenges on some days, the boss fights are really challenging but they are really entertaining especially with some of their hilarious dialogue.The whole multiplayer experience seems great because you can grab a group of friends and participate together fighting evil pig thingies.OverallOverall, this game is pretty good and it's definitely worth the price. The game is still undergoing some updates, however don't let the overall look take away from the great experience that it has to offer.7.5"
