,Recommended,434570,25590716,"Posted: 19 September, 2016",all,Atlas,"First, I would like to give a personal thank you to BigCorporation.You are single-handedly THE funniest, kindest developer I have ever met.The Game:""Hmm, Blood and Bacon; it's only a dollar and it has 'Overwhelmingly Positive' reviews...  Screw it, I'm gonna buy it.""Ten minutes later and 3 of my friends own it and we are having a BLAST!Blood and Bacon is an experience in revenge.  The Farmer, the lord and savior, is in a bit of a pickle. So what does he do?  He recruits you and anyone else to take back the farm!  There's guns, grenades, power-ups; and BLOOD AND BACON!  Running around and shooting the crap out of dozens of pigs is just plain fun.  Play with some friends and this game is seriously a hilarious joyride.  The voice acting is absolutely my favorite part, and everything the farmer says made my group laugh out loud many a time.  Plenty of secrets exist in the game too.  There are cool little quirks and discoveries to be made, and discovering these is another little part of the ""magic"" that this little gem exudes.TLDR;This game is $.99 not on sale and is totally worth every penny, with $4.00 you can buy it for 3 friends and have an awesome afternoon (assuming you don't keep playing it every other day like we do) of blood, guts, and BACON!"
