,Recommended,434570,23862300,"Posted: 27 June, 2016",all,ⒷⓇⓊⒸⒺ ⒻⓄⓇⓉⒺ,"At first, I assumed this game was a shovelware left 4 dead rip-off, but in time, after playing 31 in-game days, I've learned that this game in fact stands very well on its own. It's a comedic survival shooter with well timed horror elements and gross-out visual puns. Most of the comedic moments are due to the (somehow alive) farmer pinned to the wall with a pitchfork. He's very deadpan and sardonic, and has a voiceline for each day (at least as far as I've played). The shooter elements work very well. You have a primary weapon with ammo management and a secondary with infinite bullets. At the start of each game, you pick your two weapons and head out to the farm.The main antagonists (and only antagonists) of this game are pigs. Boars to be exact. It's hard to tell why they're rampaging, since the plot is very light, but they seem to at least have eaten steroid-laced grain that the farmer kept in his silo (which he tells you for some reason). They can be dismembered and keep going, but ultimately you can gib them completely. This adds another gameplay elements. The gibs have physics and can be kicked, shot or melee'd around, and if you get them into a meat grinder, you can turn them into useful items like ammo, grenades and various buffs for your character. There are a variety of different pigs to kill with different variables and weaknesses.Now, for the strangely well timed horror elements. Every now and then, you have a night mission. During these missions, strangely muted and bitcrushed music plays, which is quite unsettling, and many of the pigs have been replaced with skeleton pigs. I have no idea why this freaked me out. Maybe it's the moments when you feel alone and can't find that last pig, just for it to magically appear behind you. Maybe it's the insanely creepy metal pigs when you get up close to them. I'll tell you one thing; the first boss is pretty ♥♥♥♥ing scary.I give this game an 8/10 for surprising me. It has great potential and somehow managed to work out despite how it looks and sounds. I'd wager to give this a 9, but I think it would need a little bit of extra content and gameplay polish for that.Definitely recommended."
