,Recommended,434570,23457116,"Posted: 8 June, 2016",all,Super,"Over 100 Days of Pork Power-Pounding Pleasure!PROS:http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=699946079http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=699946117http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=699946157~10 Decent weapons to choose from. They serve their own purpose and some combinations are far, far better than others.Each of the 4 or so powerups you can obtain in the game (the rest of the obtainable items being ammo or grenades) are actually quite good and do their job well.A toaster from 1973 can run this game, even with hundreds of entities on the screen.+/-:A few miscellaneous bugs here and there such as shoving dead bodies making the enemy counter go up, or ammo counters glitching out for a couple weapons. I've yet to encounter any bugs that break the game or make general play impossible, however.The Farmer's voice acting is less-than-stellar (although this might be intentional as the game is a bit tongue-in-cheek) and the dialogue he speaks repeats from Days ~41 through 99. If you're like me and breeze through the days quite fast, it may get a little bit incredibly excessively grating.The game is still being updated by the developer (for better or worse). At the time of writing this review, the developer is currently working on 4-player co-op mode (current version is up to 2 player only)The graphics are early PS2-tier (again, for better or worse) and there are only two or three music tracks in the entire game (only one during the actual day gameplay).CONS:The final weapon you obtain (a rocket launcher than sends a rocket into the air to rain down airstrikes) is actually quite disappointing and practically unusuable. For its high blood cost at the grinder for one rocket drop and a high spread for the airstrikes, its damage is lackluster at best and almost nonexistent at worst. Even on revenge day it barely kills anything.Bosses repeat after day 20 in a predictable pattern (until day 100) with only one more boss and/or a palatte swap depending on which day is repeated. This combined with the general flow of the Days can lead to repititve gameplay, which even the almost satirical tone of the game may not be able to alleviate.As with the gameplay, the replayability may stagnate over time due to the nature of the game.CONCLUSIONFor the incredibly costly and expensive full retail price of 99 cents, you may find better or worse than this game easily. However, as I see it you would be hard-pressed to find a cheap game of cheap mindless violence more addicting and fun than this game (unless it's a flash game for free or something.) I would immediately recommend this game to anyone who is looking to spend anywhere from 20 minutes to 2 days doing something that requires nothing more than a mighty thirst for bloodshed.-I would like to point out that the developer BigCorporation has contacted me personally to thank me for supporting the game. The dev is friendly and actually listens to the feedback given to them in the discussions or otherwise. The developer's contacting me and any information given has not changed the opinions and information presented in this review in any way."
