,Recommended,434570,21262999,"Posted: 16 February, 2016",all,|-MC_JP-|THE LEGACY OF TERROR,"Before I start I wanna say big thanks to the developer ""BigCorporation"" for taking 2 hours of his personall time in order to fully get the game working for me. A great step by step plan to figure out what was wrong and he knows what he is doing! The developer is a friendly person who cares about his game and it's players!so now my sort of In depth review of Blood and bacon.Where do I start? You play as a own chosen character who needs to survive in a farm attacked by evil piggies. Lucky the character isn't named ""angry bird"" haha! Jokes aside this game is just straight fun and stress relieving.  The game is an arena shooter that puts you against various pigs or better boars. Tiny, normal, big, undead, bones etc.-Weapons-The game has 4 Handguns and 7 main weapons. Ranging from Ak's and Uzis to pistols and grenade launchers. Power ups are present like hand grenades and melee boosters.-Area-As stated the game sets place on a ""deserted"" farm, well deserted is a big word since waves and waves of bacon ready yummy pigs are coming your way and the farmer which is impaled with a pitchfork. He adds a great humor to the game aswell. The farm has a few interesting spots. The grinder allows you to dump the corpses in the bacon o fier and this will give you handy pickups later in the game. The electric fence gives a great killzone in the middle of the map, the farmhouse is the place for weapons and missions, and you can heal with a waterwell.-special events-Ingame: every week has 1 revenge day. This day gives you infinite explosive ammo, ideal for filling the grinder. On the 10th day there will be a boss fight, with various funny bosses.Night battles are scary because of the limited light you have. Adding into the suspense.Every mission is a day and can last from 30 seconds to 10 minutes or more (mostly boss battles do take some time) So this is a great short take a break game.Pros:+ Great stress relieving shoot-em up area shooter+ Handy for playing in short breaks (lunch break, or a little stress reliever trough the day)+ Cheaper than a pack of chewing gum+ The developer is a great person who took 2 hours of his personal time to aid me in my problem. Running through all the scenarios and fixing the problem we had.+ Shoot pigs ask questions later+ Environmental attacks adds into the imersion+ Great oldschool simple shoot em up game.Cons:- Sadly no multiplayer yet. Would have been awesome- Could be a bit repetitive for some people because of limited content (please do note that this is a 99 cent game and not a 60$ huge budget title)Overall score: 8/10.---original notes----Reworked my review after the developer contacted me. After working all night to get the problem fixed I must say the dev is working hard to help everyone. And besides, I love this slaughter game. So thumbs up!"
