76561198074867492,Recommended,434570,25825586,"Posted: 2 October, 2016",all,Dragon Force,"A crazy game with furious pigs!P.S. Not recommended for vegans.TitleBlood and BaconDeveloperBig CorporationPublisherGrunge Games LTDRelease1 February 2016Graphics3DGenreFPSPrice€0,99Rating7/10The game.Blood and Baconis a highly stylized team-based shooter game. This game is an antibiotic for what ails indie FPS's. No half-baked concoction, no stiff controls, no detrimentally-repetitive waves, and perhaps most importantly, no zombies. Well, no traditional zombies. Instead it’s undead livestock, refreshing enough to feel different, and dead enough not to upset animal rights groups.The plot (+):starting off in the game, you are a police officer going to a barn over some mysterious activity, once you arrive at the barn you find the farmer nailed to the wall as he says it was the pigs that is making the farm a bad place. It's your job to survive wave after wave of evil pigs to bring peace back to the farm.Gameplay.The barn is the hub where you talk to the farmer every day, you will also see weapons on the walls to use against the pigs, and unlock more weapons as the days progress. You leave the barn to fight a huge horde of pigs - the best part aboutBlood and Baconis blowing them to pieces before they attack you. This game makes it a beautiful sight having pig guts fly all around the map, and you’re able to punch the dead pigs into a grinder to give you ammo, grenades, or even milk. Along with this game being a horde mode, many days will be different from how you play. Some of the days can either be at night, which brings out skeleton pigs, days with unlimited ammo, or days having you fight bosses.The graphics (+):they are old-looking, but in my opinion kinda charming. The ak-47 looks like something taken out of theCounter-Strike 1.6era, but the game plays like a fast-paced, crazy FPS. They was obviously made this was to be more of a humorous type of game.The story (-):doesn't make much sense and the voice-acting is a little bad, but who cares. This is a game mostly focused on silly gameplay where you murder hordes of monsters and animals for a while. This game actually had more depth then I expected for the price, lots of characters to pick between, some sort of upgrade system, new unlockable levels, cheat mode enabled once you clear thirty waves, and so on.Multiplayer.One amazing thing about this game is the multiplayer mode; you are able to fight pigs not just by yourself, but with people around the world, who you meet to kill endless waves of pigs to paint the farm red with pig blood.If you just want a little bit of fun alone or with friends (co-op) then by all means pick this up.Just don't expect to much in terms of graphics or story.Blood and Bacondoes have 100+ levels though, so gameplay-wise it actually have a lot of content for the asking price.Positive points. (+)Price.I'm not vegan, what's obviously important.The game need minimum requirements for PC.Wise and easy gameplay.Old graphics but very kind.Multiplayer makes this game a lot of fun (up to 6 players).Negative points. (-)Repetitive scenes.The story is weak (but does it matter?).A very small soundtrack.For a cheap horde mode game, it can be argued as the best horde game. While most games are going for €5, this game boasts free DLC and updates for a while, and it was a successful port from xbox360.Blood and Baconis an outstanding game to go back to from time to time, and you can play it in short bursts showing that you do not need to buy the most expensive and beautiful looking games to have a blast.Blood and Baconis a game that is recommended to have in your steam library due to how much fun can be had, for such a cheap deal."
