,Recommended,434570,26671208,"Posted: 18 November, 2016",all,cyanide_headache,"Slaying evil and demonic farm animals while being guided by a dismembered farmer impaled to the barn wall with a pitchfork. What is not to love?This game has simple controls, decent graphics for what it is, a variety of in-game options for fun (not just shooting, but frying animals with electric fences, pushing them in to meat-grinders, etc).  The dialogue is funny, the camera options are interesting (you can set your view to one of three options) and there are single and multi-player options.The game is pretty up front about what it is and what it isn't pretending to be.  So, despite a small amount of time in terms of game-play, I feel that I can say that this is not the type of game that will disappoint. If you enjoy the first five minutes, it will only get better from there."
