76561198408671944,Recommended,434570,35103617,Posted: 21 September,all,DevlinBlack666,"I’ve put about an hour into Blood and Bacon. Time flies when you’re gone pigg’n.  Its 99 cents. I honestly thought about refunding it because I know at some point the joke will wear thin.  Then I remember the time I bought Dinosaur Hunt for 99 cents.Only to swiftly refund Dinosaur hunt in less than an hour. When compared to Dinosaur Hunt, Blood and Bacon is a masterpiece. It’s rare that I delve into the 99 cent bargain bin,  this would be my third dip in the pool. Behind Dinosaur Hunt and Street Racing Syndicate.I picked up Street Racing Syndicate on sale for 99 cents and I kept it. It’s likely I’m going to keep Blood and Bacon as well.  Because it’s fun and unlike other games in its price bracket it actually delivers everything it promises by the bucket load.It looks like a Left 4 Dead clone at surface level. It plays like an odd mix of Killing Floor and Serious Sam with lots of blood and lots of bacon.  It’s the whole hog and it more than lives up to its title of the goriest indie game ever.It runs smooth, and I’m confident it could even run on a toaster with no lag.  The option of multiple camera angles to suit multiple styles of play is quite a neat little feature though I couldn’t see myself playing B&B in anything but first person.If I had 5 other people to play with I’d gift them 10 copies. It’s just that good. B&B is the real haram.  The game was released in 2016 but it looks more like a 2008 game.  It’s got multiplayer, online multiplayer and co-op which is awesome.Getting the resolution to fit the screen right was a bit fiddly but after some optimization the game runs smoothly at a crispy 60FPS without any lag.  Makes me weirdly reminiscent about that movie “Razorback’ and if you’ve seen it you’ll understand why.I don’t know… there’s something about blasting the **** out of a razorback that brightens up my whole day. Godless **** eating vermin.  B&B only fails insofar as it doesn’t appear to have a steam workshop or any mods, which is a massive albeit liveable shame.On some level I can’t help but feel the game would have been better suited to lambs, goats, emus, walruses… the possibilities for mods are endless.  The day/night cycle is a nice touch and damn am I glad they gave you a way to heal in single player.The choice of playable characters is pretty hilarious, stereotypical and borders on the edges of racist and absurd.  Johnny Blood in particular. There’s no conceivable way I will get to the 100th way by myself, even on the easiest difficulty and I’m fine with that.The meat grinder is an interesting mechanic though if I’m supposed to kick meat into the grinder and the developer of the game forget to even map a kick button then that’s not my problem and it honestly should’ve been patched by now.Weapon variety is basic although perfectly serviceable, even if I still haven’t gotten the hang of the electric fence.There are a variety of 13 enemies, 12 bosses and 1 secret boss scattered throughout 100+ levels and the game accommodates between 2-6 players I’m told.It’s a fun weekend distraction for you and a few friends for less than the combined total of a cup of coffee with serviceable weapons, a variety of enemies with zero lag and maximum challenge.  From where I’m sitting, its hog heaven!"
