,Recommended,434570,24647267,"Posted: 31 July, 2016",all,UIRR | Kazzer,"Simple, gory, chaotic swine-slaying spree.I wasn't expecting much for $0.99 when this came in my queue of recommendations but I was pretty surprised at how entertaining it is. It's no Doom or anything, but for the money you'll find a pretty decent game here. From the endless barage of enemies (actually of varying types too, as the game progresses) to the dialogue of the farmer when you do inane things like shoot his crotch or shine the flashlight in his eyes, there's something for everyone! Okay, not really for everyone, but still...I was surprised to check the multiplayer lobbies at 1AM on a Monday morning and see a fair amount of games going so that's definitely a plus as Blood and Bacon is one of those games better enjoyed with strangers. The gameplay is competent though there isn't much to it, graphics are mediocre, and there are a few non-game-breaking bugs but from a small team for a buck, this game is more than what I'd expect. Overall, enjoyable if forgettable in the short-term; worth $1 to me but wouldn't be worth $5 if it were priced as such."
