,Recommended,434570,26133215,"Posted: 20 October, 2016",all,Decus,"I wasn't expecting to like this game as much as I did but with 19 hours and 35/36 achievements under my belt, it's a surprisingly cathartic game to play. Definitely worth the buy for 79 pence.For the gameplay, it's fairly simple: shoot pigs until the day ends then talk to the farmer and start the next day. A lot of the rounds are very similar (though that shouldn't be a problem if you've ever played COD zombies) apart from the two boss fights  which reappear with elevated difficulty every tenth day. There are differents difficulty levels and achievements to keep the game interesting for most of your play time and, if it's your thing, there's a paint gun to draw♥♥♥♥♥♥♥with.The graphics are basically basically the same as you see on the previews so pretty much any computer should be able to run this game with 30+ fps.TL;DR: Good game for price. Buy."
