76561198001940736,Recommended,434570,28042846,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,His_Awesomeness,"IntroductionBlood and Bacon is a lighthearted single player or cooperative first/third person shooter set on a farm with zombie pigs. The gameplay is similar to Killing Floor, Left 4 Dead, and Serious Sam. The goal of the default game mode is to survive increasingly difficult waves of enemies each level. The levels vary by enemy type, ultra violent bonus revenge rounds, and occasional boss battles. The ultimate goal of the game is to purge the farm of undead pigs while unlocking new weapons, hats, and characters.Pros-101 levels of increasing difficulty-Various unlockable weapons, powerups, and cheat options-Steam achievements/Trading Cards-Excellent controller support-Free content updates by developer-Easter eggs and other secrets-Creative over the top gore-High entertainment to price ratioCons-Only one map-Charming, but dated graphics-Repetitive enemy types and bosses-Normal difficulty might not be challenging for some playersConclusionThis game is a fantastic value at $0.99 and I highly recommend it to anybody who enjoys games like Killing Floor or any FPS featuring hundreds of enemies. Blood and Bacon offers a lot of entertainment for the price of admission, but don't expect next generation graphics or a fully developed storyline. It costs less than a weapon skin from games like that and it's already more entertaining than a similarly priced candy bar."
