,Recommended,434570,32831117,Posted: 26 June,all,Reamees the Red,"By far the best game on Steam at the time of writing. A gripping storyline, flawless voice acting and infinite replay value.The protagonists attempt to survive in a dystopian society, where a mysterious seemingly immortal figure known only as The Farmer holds them hostage at Ground Zero of a biology experiment gone wrong. This experiment, presumably performed by The Farmer, has created a race of super Suidae, which now run rampant at The Farm.One of many theories to explain how all of this came to be, is that the game is biblical in nature. The Farmer represents the son of god himself. He is the shepherd and our heroes are His flock. This is made obvious by the way The Farmer is visually represented - impaled to the wall of a barn. This is a clear reference to the crucifixion of christ and as He was born in a barn, it also serves as a symbol of rebirth. This explains the borderline divine abilities of The Farmer: He survives for months, despite being impaled to a wall with a pitchfork. He can open and close doors with his mind. He can conjure up weapons and ammo. He is impervious to both bullets and explosives. He sees and knows everything that happens on The Farm.It is theorised that the protagonists are undergoing purification in purgatory. They seek to eradicate their sins, which are represented by the swine, with help from their lord and saviour The Farmer. There are certain collectibles in the game, which can only be reached by dying to the swine. This means that The Farmer rewards martyrdom. We must learn from these brave warriors and seek to rid ourselves of sin in their wake. This game has shown me the way through the valley of darkness and helped me see the light. It is never too late to embrace the guidance of The Farmer. We must repent.10/10 found Jesus via pig killing game"
