,Recommended,434570,25579763,"Posted: 18 September, 2016",all,ThePCGamer101,"DISCLAIMER: This is a first impressions review, and NOT a full review, if you want a full review, then please read better reviews then mineTHE BLOODIEST INDIE GAME ON THE MARKET... maybeIf PETA was the censorship board, Blood and Bacon would definitely be banned for animal cruelty on a virtual videogameAlthough I do not support animal cruelty and I fully support PETA (to a certain extent) and that I am a vegan (yes, a vegan playing a gory bloody game about boars being bloodily mutalated for no apparent reason), I am not easily offended by Blood and Bacon's setting and gameplay, in fact, I love it!Blood and Bacon is a game developed by Big Corporation and published by Grudge Games LTD.Blood and Bacon is a really fun Left 4 Dead type game, even as much as copying the UI from the console versions of Left 4 Dead and Left 4 Dead 2 (according to console sources). Blood and Bacon was the best game I've seen for its price for a very long time, especially when playing with friends (which sadly I do not have)You are in barn with its farmer stuck to the barn wall with a pitchfork in him and a leg chopped off (no biggy). And each day you have to try and kill the required amount of boars/pigs by shooting them, juggling them and then shooting them, electrocuting them or throwing them into a mincer. Each day, more and more boars show upAfter a certain amount of days, a boos boar shows up where you shoot the living hell out of it. This happens every day in the game. The game can get boring and repetitive after a while of playing in solo, however, the game is extremely fun to play with your friends in co-op (which sadly I do not have any friends)You can play online co-op with other people, but some of the players are so brain dead that they stay in the barn and the level doesn't play or they die too quicklyBlood and Bacon is really fun game to play. So badly made that it is good. The game surprisingly has full of good humor with some challenging and difficult levels and although the game is horribly made (in terms of graphics, A.I. and gameplay), the game is ridiculously cheap for only 0.99 EUR without any sales. With sales, this game can go as cheap as 0.74 EUR (that's how much I paid for this game)However, Blood and Bacon's graphics are not that great. Some graphics are ugly to look at and the UI is pretty ugly to look at and the game offers a very small soundtrack. Not that much music happening while playing which is a shameI wouldn't recommend Blood and Bacon if it was priced higher than 1 EUR, however for the price it is offering and the options the game offers and the bloody gory fun you can have while playing alone and especially with friends, I would definitely recommend Blood and Bacon to anyoneRECOMMENDED :)NOMINATED FORTHE ""BEST USE OF A FARM ANIMAL"" AWARDFOR THE STEAM AWARDS 2016"
