,Recommended,434570,21577998,"Posted: 1 March, 2016",all,ExiledAlchemist,"After completing the game I knew I just had to come back and edit my review. Don't worry this updated review is going the be spoiler free.I got this game after seeing not only the video, the price, but also the number of positive reviews.After playing it for a short time I became hooked. I just had to play this game to the end and I did. Blood and Bacon is an addictive and fun arena style wave shooter. You play as a hired gun with one job at hand to rid the farm of an army of undead hogs.  As you progress new weapons and items unlock, and at the same time enemies get bigger, stronger, and grow in number. After so many days you will encounter a boss battle. Each boss battle becomes more intense and challenging making victory feel more rewarding. With the number of options from all the unlockables players are able to come up with various combinations of how to handle each day.As for story it stays very simple and instead focuses more on the gameplay. That isn't a bad thing if you are a fan of games like Doom, or Serious Sam. The music is very catchy and really gets you in the mood to play. The graphics are closer to classic shooter style from the N64/PS2 era that just fits the theme of the game so well. In honestly it's more of a breath of fresh air compared to other modern games. The game has an art style that I haven't seen since Conker's Bad Fur Day. In all honestly it's just another reason why I enjoy this game so much.After all that said I still highly recommend this game. It's not only addictive but also a great time killer. So if you have the shekels to spare please pick it up. You can't go wrong with this one."
