,Recommended,434570,20905273,"Posted: 1 February, 2016",all,Zach Fett,"Such a fun game. I played a ton of this back when it was on Xbox 360, and I plan to put a lot more time into it now that it's on PC. It's an extremely cheesy, ridiculous, disgustingly bloody game where you run around shooting pigs, kicking their body parts into a grinder to buy ammo/grenades/milk/melee boosters/etc, and talk to a farmer with a close relationship with a pitchfork.It starts off slow, but once you hit the Princess Blubbergut boss fight it all starts to get much, much more bloody and crazy. Early on you're only dealing with 10-20 pigs in a day, but after a while it'll crank up the difficulty with 50+ pigs at a time. Revenge Days are the best days of the week, giving you infinite explosive ammo and tons of pigs to gib for the grinder.There's a decent amount of weapons, 100 days (levels), and three characters to unlock. There's a lot of content here for $1! I'd highly recommend it if you enjoy horde-style games, ridiculous gore, and a game that doesn't take itself seriously.The only issues I've had with the game are not being able to rebind keys*, not able to edit the camera while using a keyboard (but you can with a controller by pressing Start), the black border around the screen no matter the resolution you use, some sound issues with gunshots, and sadly that co-op (which was on the Xbox 360 version) is not in this current PC port. However, the developer has said he's interested in doing it, but it sounds like it'll only be possible if the game sells well enough.The rest of the issues I'm sure will be fixed sooner or later. The default keybindings are fine (minus X being use, instead of E), but I'd still like to be able to rebind*.Also, the developer is extremely cool. If you have any issues, just hit him up, he responds really quickly and will try to help you fix any problems! I hope he'll bring some of his other games to Steam one day soon, I'd kill a thousand skeleton pigs just to play DeadKings (with the multiplayer included, hopefully!) on PC.*Edit: Rebinding has now been added in the most recent patch. You just have to go to your game folder, find the KEYBOARD folder, then edit the KEYS_BU.txt to your liking. Once you're done rename that file to KEYS.txt and it'll work just fine!"
