,Recommended,434570,27925893,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,Stomedy,shoot pigs for bacons
,Recommended,434570,29076456,Posted: 6 January,all,Toyfan1: You N'Wah!,"In Short:This game is not what you're expecting. it's so much more.Get it.Even if you don't like killing ruthless zombie animals, support this developer.it's cheap. Goes on sale for even cheaper. It's well worth the money.Spoilers: These spoilers talk about in-game unlocks and Bosses. If you want to go in blind and want to wait and see what the game has to offer, unlock wise, don't read them.The camera systemNow, before I start with the game review- The camera system in this game is amazi- No.It's more than amazing.It's perfect.No questions asked. You have 3 camera presents.First person (camera 1) , Over the Shoulder (Camera 2), and Third person (Camera 3)""Wow that's pretty cool"" you might ask.It's cooler than cool. it's ice-cold.Because you can EDIT EACH CAMERA.Do you want a top-down view of the entire map? You can do that.Do you want a foot angle where you can see everything from an ant's perspective? It's possible.You want a crotch camera where you can see nothing but your character's crotch? Do it.It's SO un to experiment with the camera angles.You can even edit the HUD. Little Big Planet Karting styleSure, Elder Scrolls may have their customizable 3rd person camera mod, but that's only one camera angle!Shadow of Morridor has a neat cinematic mode, but that's not very action-oriented.This is perfect.And with the combination of HUD placement, you can make this game feel like L4D2 had babies with metal gear solid.It's perfect. What more could you ask for?To startI saw this game and figured it would be just several asset flips.Boy was I completely wrong.The ONLY thing about this game that is bad, is the graphics and models.Everything else is Flawless.Absolute master piece.In Depth; GameplayThis is basically Devil Daggers, but it won't make you slice your eyes out.The gist is you run around a fairly small map, shooting enemies (zombie pigs) every 10 levels is a boss fight.Guns are somewhat varied. Some Pistols are very inferior to others, while the primaries have much more substance and variety,The Colt 1911 is pretty standard, nothing special but the model looks REALLY nice. 15 ammo, and fair amount of damage.Silenced pistol is pretty ok, much like the Colt but as im aware, it doesn't Aggro (Anger, Target) pigs.Revolver is pretty pointless. very small magazine, yet it has some good damage.But the paintball gun...OOoooooh my god, this paintball gun. Best. Unlimted ammo, great spammability, and the best part- you can choose what color of paintball you shoot by reloading. I always use it.Primaries:The AK is just like the Colt 1911. Very neat model, but all around good weapon.M4, just like the ak, but a better model. obviously there are differences stat wise. But again, over all good weapon.UZI, bullet hose. nuff saidShotgun, it actually got a buff. it's really tasteful to use, and you feel absolutely badass using it.Nuke. Kill a bunch of things with a nuke, low ammo, very high damage.P90, much like the UZI, yet i think has less ammo, more accuracy.They are all pretty balanced and fun. I spice it up every level.Traps, and consumables.No no, not the one-time use consumables you have to pay for- these items, such as grenades, bulkify, and Milk.These boost you're character significantly.Bulkify, 1hit melee kill pigs, Milk makes you go insanely fast and jump high. it's VERY fun to combo each.Traps on the other hand, are niche. You'll either lure a group off pigs to the center of the map to electrocute them with an electric fence, or you lure them into a grinder which helps you get the boost items.Blood and bacon consists of a many types of enemies, I couldn't list them all.You have big pigs, you have silver pigs, you have armored pigs, Skeleton pigs, GHOST PIGSInnocent non-zombified pigs, this game has ityou even have boss pigs.Boss 1Big mean grumpy pig. He is a big pig with HILARIOUS writing.boss 2Princess. The Farmer's biggest and meanest. She's fat, ♥♥♥♥♥ and pukes. Pretty hilarious to fight.That's it on the enemies and guns- but Im not done yet.over 50 levels. That's just the single player.There's multiplayer, Double co-op, 4 Mode, and even a co-op Horde mode.There's even EVENTS ike the Halloween Horde mode.This game has SOOOOO Much depth despite being 99c and or cheaper.The StoryStory is pretty basic. Farmer did some nasty stuff. But the writing. Oh my god is the writing SO ******* GOOD.Just shoot the farmer. It's hilarious. The farmer blends so well into the story. His personality, his quotes, all excellent.The Bosses interactions, and background are great too.I barely can spoil anything story wise.Graphics and AestheticBlood and bacon has that retro-1990s to 2000s look. Very few polygons, stretched images. it feels like an homage to that type of gaming history. But if you didn't experience gaming at that time, the game doesn't look too good.The graphics make this game instantly dated, despite it being released a year ago.Animations are pretty bad, but at times they can be funny. Such as being dead, and still being able to reload your gun.Reloading when you have full ammo, punching pigs, jumping high, etc.overall fine, if you can handle the poor animations.Various NotesThe Developer (s). Now, Im not sure if this game has more than one developer. But the one who is on the forums, and updating the game.They're brilliant. They're nice, responsive, and overall good developers.UpdatesSurprisingly, this game is updated often.Halloween updates, Christmas goodies, balancing, 4Player mode was even added, along with Horde mode.Just recently, all 1-42 levels (Beginner levels) were reworked to be more challenging.I'm always surprised to see this game get updates because you wouldn't expect that many updates out of a 99cent game.hatsThis game has hats.yes hats.that's all.Hats.Final ThoughtsThis game is a buck. If you go by the Dollar per Hour mentality It's well worth it.Overall, it's a good, well-made game for a flat price.I am halfway done with the game, and I have 10 hours. I expect to completely beat it by 25hs.That's not counter multiplayer, events, or trying to get all the hats.It's definitely worth the money at 99c or below, you will get SO much out of this game.Regardless-I was very surprised how much content, innovatively, and polish this game had for being a dollar.Blood and Bacon gets a special gold star from me."
