,Not Recommended,434570,24662910,"Posted: 1 August, 2016",all,altitudinem,"This game was pretty entertaining, for a couple of hours. I mean, don't get me wrong, blasting the living meatchunks out of pigs is great, but that's all you do. For the entire game. It's so repetitive and mundane... Oh yeah, sure, there are bosses, but the same concepts -- Even the same animations and sound bytes -- are re-used.Oh, and one more thing, spoilers ahead.The thing that tipped me over the edge -- and I mean OVER the edge of edges -- was the final ""boss."" If you can even call it a boss. The final level that had such a massive build up was literally a group of harmless, mindless ""friendly"" pigs. When you kill all of them in a mess of bloody pig parts, like the game has taught you to do for about 6 hours, you're punished for it. Then guess what, your game restarts! That's right, you went from an astonishing day 101 back to an insufferably easy day 1.Now that's out of the way, we can talk about the mechanics. The game is basically a crude re-creation of CoD Zombies with a bit of Left for Dead thrown in there as well. The graphics aren't great, but oh well, games have limitations. Let's not forget about the ""game cheats."" Why have them? Did the developers know that people would get tired of doing the same task over and over? Well, they certainly thought ahead on that one.Anyway, it was an interesting concept, and let's be honest, who didn't draw some naughty things on the walls with the paintball gun?"
