,Recommended,434570,22732390,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Grenadeh,"I don't even know what I just played.Blood and Bacon is a wave survival game on a farm where you fight lots, and lots, and lots of pig-type species.Obviously this is an indie game and not very full featured, but I paid about $.90 for it so whatever.The graphics feel ancient, like N64 era, but it's not that big of a deal. The sound design isn't anything out of the ordinary but is satisfying, especially when you use the rocket launcher. Most of the guns have incomplete or basically non existent reload animations, and you can reload constantly even when your magazine is full.  The voice acting for the farmer is completely awful, maybe on purpose, but the voice acting for bosses and the sounds made by the pigs and grinder are spot on. There is some occasional humor to the game, most of it coming from the Farmer's lines, the bosses and hidden messages sprawled about the farm, but the game itself is pretty funny considering you are basically murdering a ton of hogs and pigs and undead pigs.In many ways this game is like survival mode in L4D, just very barebones. Each pig you kill, you can push it's gibs or entire body into a grinder that magically turns them in to resources so you can buy grenades, revive pills, milk, ammo, nukes, and superstrength.The only negative thing I have to say about the actual gameplay is that survival mode takes a long time. 100 days. If you are actually pushing everything in to the grinder, it takes quite a while to get through each day. Every 10 days my co op partner and I would be like ""30 days and it's not over? Maybe 50 because we have like 2 guns left to unlock? Maybe 75? It's 100!?""  All in all though, sure, it's worth 90 cents for a few hours of fun until you get tired of it. I don't know what the original price of the game was but I'd still pay a few dollars more for it."
