,Recommended,434570,29554077,Posted: 28 January,all,Din0kid,"This is a very good game. The presentation and design are amazing, I love the artstyle. It's a very innovative game, one for the ages. It's basically this generation's Pong, a game universally loved and adored, a game that spawns countless more. The ability to change the camera view is ground breaking. The weapon variety is astounding. The music fits the incredible, desolate setting very, very well. Without giving too much away, the story is mind-blowing. You are stranded on an intergalatic farm, hurtling through space. Your navigator, ""The Farmer,"" has been severly injured and left to die on the side of a barn. Each day you must hunt down the pigs which threaten your base, and fight to uncover clues about what happened to the Earth you've left behind. I can see this game being very influential in the development of games to come.Did I mention it has Co-op? The way the story and atmosphere lends itself to multiplayer is astounding. Everything about this game is amazing. It is truly a masterpiece, the likes of which video gaming has never seen. The Mona Lisa, Beethoven's symphonies, none of those works of art hold a candle to this generation-defining magum opus. One does not ""play"" this game. One experiences it, lives it. The immersive graphics assist the game in drawing the player, defending their last bastion, this floating farm, from these otherworldly invaders. Words cannot describe the sensations this game has made me feel."
