76561198070256007,Recommended,434570,27163433,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Red_Lunar_Shade,"As of writing this review it is during the steam game awards and let me tell you I wish you were able to pick 2 options because this game definitely hands-down should win the ""Best use of a farm animal"" award and definitely the ""I thought this game was cool before it won an award"" award.Now onto the review.This game first came out for Xbox 360 probably a year or two back if im right and I had a great time with it all the way to the end. Now I'm here to tell you this PC version though and let me tell you there is so much that's different here that it feels like a new game entirely.Blood and Bacon is a game where you play as one of 6 characters, you go to a farm to find a farmer in a barn stuck to the wall with a pitchfork in his gut and missing leg, every new day you get to in the game the farmer will tell you some tips on how to survive and over time you will either learn to love him or hate him, and every day you come to kill all the pigs each day and then you talk to the farmer at the end of the day to start the next one.Now I'm sure your wondering, ""why is this game so Overwhelmingly Positive if it is such a simple and small game?"" Well if you have seen the trailer before looking at this review I will tell you that it is definitely the blood bath you see in it. With now up to 4 player coop where even more pigs spawn in depending on the number of players in your game you can find one hell of a time. And trust me, some days you will literally see nothing but ""Blood and Bacon"" at the end of some days.This game has lots of unlocks and a TON of secrets or fun things to do around the farm. Some you will find on your own or learn from the farmer. Meanwhile the farmer has lots of fun and interesting quotes to say depending on finding secrets on the farm, shooting the farmer, or from simply flashing your flashlight in his face.And customizable camera angles is one of the 'bigger' features this game has. With three different camera angle options on top of customizing them yourself and moving the cameras allows you to make the game first or third-person or whatever you see fit.The bosses are fun and definitely challenging to learn and do for your first time and I am sure you may think 'wtf' on day 10, then 'what the hell' on day 20 leading all the way to the final day where you will definitely need some help because these bosses are of a Dark Souls quality here. Which comes onto the second topic here...Multiplayer is definitely a fun blast to play and with the new 6-player horde map you can unlock even more secrets and one of the now 9 characters they have in this game now. Not only that but this game also has....keyword here.....free hats for your characters if you find keys which requires you to look around for secrets and such. But there are also other secrets leading to the farmer to say some 'clever' farm jokes and even sing a song.When you play this game you will DEFINITELY see pig parts flying around and definitely some blood flying all over the farm. And yes, you do fight hundreds of pigs at a time some days and revenge days are where this game really shines.Trust me, this game is worth it for it's 0.99 price and at the time of this review 0.79 price. Definitely worth the dollar price and why would you ignore this game during it's sale? I have bought this game many times and I never regret a single time I purchased this game. And by the time your done you will see pigs in a new light and definitely have a hunger for BLOOD & BACON."
