,Recommended,434570,29245911,Posted: 14 January,all,FuriousUnagi,"(5) Great(4) Good(3) Regular(2) Bad(1) Terrible(0) AwfulBasic ReviewA mindless wave survival FPS made to be played with friends. Cheesy, funny and unexpected. Worth its price.Full ReviewBlood and Bacon (BnB) takes wave survival to a whole new level: instead of the standard ""survive against waves of monsters/zombies"", BnB tasks you to survive againstmonster/zombie pigs!It's a game meant to be funny and laughable.Wave survival games, as I see it, are meant to be multiplayer games. I couldn't see my self doing the same task over and over alone. It gets repetitive quickly, but that's the point of it: to see how much you can endure.The community is scarce, but everytime I'd play I'd see like 3 other servers online, so it has its followers.I played with a couple of friends and it was a funny experience. I'd classify this little gem as casual and mind-numbing, intended for you to play to chill and laugh.As for graphics, they are outdated, but that's the charm of it. Sounds are repetitive, just never mind.I'd recommend it for it's price, but only if you can find someone to play with you occasionally."
