,Recommended,434570,29647954,Posted: 2 February,all,Rev3rEND,"Don't go into this expecting Fallout, DOOM, or hell even Serious Sam.  Keep your expectations in check and you'll have fun.  The mechanics are very simple but work: every ten days is a ""boss"" fight, you slowly unlock more and more weapons as you progress through the days, use the grinder to grind up the pigs to fill ammo, grenades, etc etc.  That's it.  Oh, and of course survive.Controls a bit too twitchy and exact, as in your character will move at a single speed with no build up as soon as you hit a  direction and stop dead in his tracks the moment you let go.  A bit jarring but they could be worse.  Graphics are subpar, audio is weak, the Farmer's quips and phrases are entertaining at first but get tiresome.But it's a buck and it works fine... and it's fun with friends.  Just do it."
